{ "cells": [ { "cell_type": "markdown", "id": "4a4a53af", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "# A/B Test analysis with Python " ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "id": "3ead686a", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "A/B testing, also known as split testing, is a method used in marketing, product development, and website optimization to compare two versions of something to determine which one performs better. It is a controlled experiment where you expose two groups (Group A and Group B) to different variations of a product, webpage, or other elements to see which one yields better results. The primary goal of A/B testing is to make data-driven decisions and optimize your strategies." ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "id": "ddfe3811", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "**Goal of A/B testing**" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "id": "8950b50a", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "A/B testing is commonly used for optimizing websites, marketing campaigns, product features, and user experiences to increase conversion rates, engagement, and overall performance." ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": 1, "id": "58c8fa98", "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "#importing Necessary Libraries \n", "import pandas as pd\n", "import datetime\n", "from datetime import date, timedelta\n", "import plotly.graph_objects as go\n", "import plotly.express as px\n", "import plotly.io as pio" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "id": "aa24a5d1", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "So we have 2 data sets one is the normal dataset(control dataset) and other is Campaign dataset (Test dataset)" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": 3, "id": "dee84281", "metadata": {}, "outputs": [ { "data": { "text/html": [ "
